<HEADLINE>
NO PLAN TO RECRUIT LEGISLATIVE SPEAKER TO FORM TICKET FOR NOW:
KMT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 21 (CNA) 05/21/07  14:53:25 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
The main opposition Kuomintang (KMT) is not planning to recruit
Legislative Yuan Speaker Wang Jin-pyng to run on a ticket with Ma
Ying-jeou, the party's presidential candidate, a KMT spokesman
said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Su Chun-pin was responding to reports by the China Times, a local
daily, which quoted ranking KMT officials as saying that in a bid
to win the 2008 presidential election, the KMT is not ruling out
the possibility of recruiting Wang to serve as Ma's running mate
even if Wang is not very enthusiastic about it.
</P>
<P>
Su said that "as of the present time, the KMT has not formally
planned to recruit Wang."
</P>
<P>
He also said that "any decisions by the party will respect the
wishes, stance and feelings of the person involved."
</P>
<P>
He stressed  that the most important  task is to promote
cooperation on all sides, adding that "KMT Chairman Wu Poh-hsiung
hopes for a Ma-Wang ticket and will do everything possible to
bring it about."
</P>
</TEXT>
